@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Cancellation Policy";
}
<div class="container">
    <h1 class="fw-bold mb-3">Cancellation Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-muted">Last updated: @DateTime.Today.ToString("dd MMM yyyy")</p>

    <p>We understand life happens. Our goal is to be fair to clients and practitioners.</p>

    <h5 class="mt-4">Rescheduling</h5>
    <p>You can reschedule free of charge up to 24 hours before your appointment.</p>

    <h5 class="mt-4">Cancellations</h5>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>24+ hours’ notice:</strong> no fee.</li>
        <li><strong>Less than 24 hours’ notice:</strong> a late-cancellation fee may apply (up to the session price).</li>
        <li><strong>No-shows:</strong> full session fee may be charged.</li>
    </ul>

    <h5 class="mt-4">Running late</h5>
    <p>If you’re late, we’ll do our best to accommodate you, but the session may need to finish at the scheduled time.</p>

    <h5 class="mt-4">How to cancel</h5>
    <p>Email <a href="mailto:hello@vitalscan.com">hello@vitalscan.com</a> or call 0400 000 000. Please include your name, appointment time, and service.</p>

    <h5 class="mt-4">Refunds</h5>
    <p>Where a fee is charged under this policy, refunds are not typically offered unless required by applicable consumer law.</p>
</div>
